The most basal group of temnospondyls is the superfamily Edopoidea . Edopoids include the Late Carboniferous genus Edops and the family Cochleosauridae . Dendrerpetontidae has also been included in Edopoidea , and is the oldest known temnospondyl family . Balanerpeton woodi is the oldest species , having been present in the Late Triassic .

In the middle of the Mesozoic, the basal temnospondyls disappeared, and the next group is the superfamily Cryptobranchidae . Cryptobranchids are known from the Late Triassic to the Early Jurassic , with the oldest known species being Globipterus elongatus , from the Lower Jurassic . Cryptobranchids have a highly elongated snout, and a large caudal fin , and also have a long, slender body.
